comments.en: This is the Ontology (V2.1) that describes the Data Access Services Information Model

comment.en: The used_Instances table in the DWH contains the measurements of the total number of instances used in the OVH storage system.
The Event table contains the basic information that characterize each event, regardless of the entities involved (Product, User, Service Component)
The dashboard_active_users table in the DWH contains the measurements of the total number of users currently registered in the ONDA web portal.
The Sentinel Product table is a "child" of the product table, inheriting its attributes and properties. In contains the specific information proper of each Copernicus Sentinel product
The used_Cores table in the DWH contains the measurements of the total number of cores used in the OVH storage system.
The User table contains the list of parameters corresponding to the users' info
The Product table in the DWH contains the list of relevant information for each product.
The products_number table in the DWH contains the measurements of the total number of products currently present in the ONDA catalogue.
The Service_component Table contains information about system components affected by all the tracked events, as well as the software components that perform the events.
The Product_event table in the DWH contains the description of all download, publication, deletion and retrieving events. Not all the fields are available for all the events.
The System_event table in the DWH contains the list of parameters that describe a system event (downtimes, TTOs, infrastructure, maintenance, etc).
The used_Ram table in the DWH contains the measurements of the total number of RAM used in the OVH storage system.
The DIAS_Download table in the DWH contains the measurements of the total number of bytes downloaded from the OVH storage in a specified range of time.
The storage_volume table in the DWH contains the measurements of the total volume (in bytes) of products present in the OVH storage.

The User Event table is a "child" of the Event table, inheriting its attributes and properties. It contains the specific information about all the events that involve the users' activities (download, orders, notifications...)
